				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					It should be noted, that you can (and probably should) sent the refresh header via the <code class='prettyprint'>header ()</code> function in PHP. As hinted to by the meta-tag's name <code class='prettyprint'>http-equiv</code>:<br />
<pre class='prettyprint lang-php linenums:0'>header ("Refresh: 5; URL=&lt;a href="http&#58;//mysite.com/"&gt;http&#58;//mysite.com/&lt;/a&gt;");</pre>
					
					<br />
					<p class='edit'>
							<strong>Edited by Christian F., 27 February 2013 - 06:43 AM.</strong>
							
